's new Threads app, meant to compete with Twitter, was available for pre-order on mobile app stores on iPhone and Android operating systems on July 5, 2023. Listed as "Threads, an Instagram app," the new program should be available in the coming days, and is described on Apple's app store as "Instagram's text-based conversation app."]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[1503955542 - Threads app]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Uber, DoorDash and Grubhub sue New York City over $18 minimum-wage law]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>据<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/2023/07/06/uber-doordash-grubhub-pay-nyc/?outputType=amp"><em>《华盛顿邮报》</em></a>报道，Uber、DoorDash 和 Grubhub 正在提起诉讼，要求颁布禁令，以阻止纽约市针对食品配送应用工人<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/new-york-city-sets-an-18-per-hour-minimum-wage-for-food-delivery-workers-193338002.html">实施 18 美元的新最低工资法</a>。这些应用程序交付平台正在要求针对新规定颁发临时限制令，该规定将于 7 月 12 日实施。 DoorDash 发言人告诉<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://edition.cnn.com/2023/07/06/business/doordash-grubhub-uber-sue-new-york-minimum-wage-law/index.html"><em>CNN</em></a> ：“我们不会袖手旁观，让这一收入标准对纽约市的顾客、商家和送货工人造成的有害影响不受控制。”</p><p>支持这项调查的工人正义项目谴责了这一新诉讼。董事 Ligia Guallpa 告诉《华盛顿<em>邮报》</em> ，“这一支持其商业模式的最新法律举措是以牺牲那些在面临巨大负担能力危机的城市中勉强生存的工人为代价的。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>纽约成为美国第一个强制规定送餐工人最低工资的城市，要求平台在 7 月 12 日之前向工人支付每小时 17.96 美元的工资，外加小费。该市的最低工资为每小时 15 美元，但额外的金额是因为送货员通常作为承包商获得报酬，因此税费较高，并且必须自掏腰包支付与工作相关的费用。根据 DCWP（纽约市消费者和工人保护部）的估计，纽约市有超过 60,000 名送餐工人，平均每小时收入为 7.09 美元。</p><p>然而，DoorDash 和 GrubHub 辩称，盈利预测是基于有缺陷的方法。 <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://iapps.courts.state.ny.us/nyscef/ViewDocument?docIndex=ub_PLUS_fhjvQeK4Hz6rTVkD/Pw==">诉讼</a>称，接受调查的工人事先被告知，目的是帮助提高送货员的工资，并提出了“正确”的答案。</p><p> Grubhub 还对监控工人的难度增加表示担忧。优步在另一起诉讼中表示，较高的最低工资将推高食品订单价格，进而损害当地餐馆的利益。</p><p>像 Uber 这样的应用服务多年来一直在与针对“零工”经济的监管进行斗争。今年早些时候， <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/court-rules-uber-lyft-keep-contractors-classification-drivers-california-054040457.html">法院裁定</a>Uber 和 Lyft 可以继续将司机视为承包商，而不是将他们重新归类为受薪员工。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/uber-doordash-and-grubhub-sue-new-york-city-over-18-minimum-wage-law-103531552.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/uber-doordash-and-grubhub-sue-new-york-city-over-18-minimum-wage-law-103531552.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> ac015833-e820-4edf-9165-6d970faa3f66</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 07 Jul 2023 10:35:31 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688723261</ingested><modified> 2023-07-07T09:47:46+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Business]]></category><category><![CDATA[Society & Culture]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="2000" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/7009b2e0-1c96-11ee-b8ff-c26c36b3ea7f" width="3000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2000" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/7009b2e0-1c96-11ee-b8ff-c26c36b3ea7f" width="3000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[New York Daily News via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A food delivery messenger is seen in Manhattan. (Luiz C. Ribeiro/New York Daily News/Tribune News Service via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[BIZ-WRK-NYC-DOORDASH-UBER-LAWSUIT-NY]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meta is working to stop deleted Threads accounts from nuking Instagram too]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>因此，您注册了一个<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/metas-threads-app-is-here-to-challenge-twitter-230039730.html">Threads</a>帐户，因为您想看看 Meta 的 Twitter 竞争对手有什么大惊小怪的。如果你认为新的社交网络不适合你，或者你想重新开始，那么删除你的 Threads 个人资料可能不是最佳选择——正如<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/7/6/23786029/instagram-threads-profiles-deleted-removing"><em>The Verge</em></a>指出的那样，这样做也会删除你的整个 Instagram 帐户。当您开设 Threads 帐户时，如果您想从照片共享应用中引入您的个人资料和圈子，则可以使用您的 Instagram 凭据进行注册。但通过这样做，您在两个平台上的帐户就会变得密不可分。</p><p> Instagram 负责人 Adam Mosseri 在<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.threads.net/t/CuXRXDdNOtH">Threads 上发表的一篇文章</a>中表示，Meta 已经意识到这个问题，目前正在寻找一种方法，允许您单独删除 Threads 帐户。该公司还在<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.threads.net/t/CuW3CzRtm9z">开发应用程序中仍然缺少的功能</a>，包括以下选项卡、主题标签、fediverse 支持和消息传递。目前，您可以停用您的 Threads 帐户以隐藏您的个人资料和内容。您还可以将您的个人资料设置为私有，或者只是删除单个线程。需要注意的是，您还可以使用未链接到 Instagram 帐户的电子邮件或电话号码注册 Threads 帐户，这样您就可以将两个平台完全分开。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Meta 推出 Threads 的时机再好不过了。 Twitter 最近做出的一些改变甚至让最狂热的用户感到沮丧。它首先<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-isnt-showing-tweets-unless-youre-logged-in-165254006.html">阻止</a>未登录的人查看推文——尽管它悄悄地回溯到要求用户登录——然后<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-puts-strict-cap-on-how-many-tweets-users-can-read-each-day-182623928.html">严格限制</a>用户每天可以看到的帖子数量。大约 1000 万用户在发布的前 7 小时内注册了 Threads 帐户，而在发布后的第一个早上，该应用程序就已经拥有了<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/threads-gained-10-million-new-users-in-seven-hours-090838140.html">3000 万用户</a>。 Threads 推出后不久，Twitter <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-threatens-to-sue-meta-over-the-new-threads-app-191141961.html">威胁要起诉 Meta</a> ，指控其挖走前员工并盗用商业机密和知识产权。在<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1677042708756439041">回应</a>有关潜在诉讼的推文时，埃隆·马斯克回答说：“竞争很好，作弊则不然。”</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/meta-is-working-to-stop-deleted-threads-accounts-from-nuking-instagram-too-094423213.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/meta-is-working-to-stop-deleted-threads-accounts-from-nuking-instagram-too-094423213.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 52362f1a-ca31-4c5f-9d44-803ee81d7d86</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 07 Jul 2023 09:44:23 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688732326</ingested><modified> 2023-07-07T12:18:51+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Social & Online Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="4000" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/4b7a9f50-1cc0-11ee-9be3-42e5edf286b7" width="6000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="4000" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/4b7a9f50-1cc0-11ee-9be3-42e5edf286b7" width="6000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Thilina Kaluthotage/NurPhoto via Getty Images]]